{{coord|58|8|34.31|N|7|59|42.95|E|type:landmark_region:NO_dim:1200|display=title}} [[File:Agder Teater fasade.JPG|thumb|The current base facility of Agder Teater]] [[File:Agder-teater-fjære1.JPG|thumb|Agder teater, scene [[Fjæreheia]], Grimstad. Theatre from outside]] [[File:Agder teater - Prinsessen på erten 2013 1.JPG|thumb|Actors from Agder teater performing «[[The Princess and the Pea]]» in schools in 2013. {{credit|Heidi Arild, Aust-Agder bibliotek og kulturformidling}}]] '''Agder Teater''' is a Norwegian [[theatre]] based in [[Kristiansand]]. It was established in 1991, and has been the regional theatre<ref>[http://kilden.com/1122/agder-teater Agder regional theatre] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318121144/http://kilden.com/1122/agder-teater |date=March 18, 2013 }}{{en icon}}</ref> for [[Agder]] since 1995.<ref name=snl-agderteater>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Agder Teater |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Agder_Teater |language=Norwegian | accessdate=3 April 2009 }}</ref>
Its first theatre director was [[Bentein Baardson]], who led the theatre from 1991 to 1994.<ref name=snl-bb>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Bentein Baardson |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Bentein_Baardson |language=Norwegian | accessdate=3 April 2009 }}</ref> [[Alex Scherpf]] has been theatre director since 2005.<ref name=snl-agderteater/>
