The '''Latin Bishopric of Coron''' or '''Diocese of Coronea''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Coronensis}}) was a [[Roman Catholic]] diocese located in the town of [[Koroni|Coron]] in [[Messenia]], [[Peloponnese]], [[Greece]],<ref name=CathHierCoron>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dc584.html "Diocese of Coron (Coronea)"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved June 16, 2016</ref><ref name=GCathCoron>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/t0570.htm "Titular Episcopal See of Coronea"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved June 16, 2016</ref> during its rule by the [[Republic of Venice]]. Following the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] conquest in 1500, it was suppressed; in 1933, it was restored as a [[titular see]].<ref name=GCathCoron />

