{{Infobox Union |name= Metall |country= [[Sweden]] |affiliation= [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation|LO]] |members= 379,000 |full_name= Swedish Metalworkers' Union |native_name= Svenska Metallindustriarbetareförbundet |image= |founded= 1888 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= January 2006 |dissolved_state= Merged into |merged_into= [[IF Metall]] |office= [[Stockholm]], Sweden |people= [[Göran Johnsson]], president |website= [http://www.metall.se www.metall.se] |footnotes= }} The '''Swedish Metalworkers' Union''' ({{lang-sv|Industrifacket Metall}}) was a [[trade union]] in [[Sweden]]. It was formed in 1888 and had a membership of 379,000.
In January 2006, the Swedish Metalworkers' Union merged with the [[Swedish Industrial Union]] to form [[IF Metall]].
