'''Zimbabwean Canadians''' are [[Canadians|Canadian citizens]] of Zimbabwean descent or a [[Zimbabwe]]-born person who resides in [[Canada]]. According to the [[Canada 2011 Census]] there were 6,425 Canadian citizens who claimed Zimbabwean ancestry and 5,065 Zimbabwean citizens residing in the country at the moment of the census.

